 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.11","title":"[audit][tests] Move owned channel state into obligation lifecycle async test closures","description":"rch-backed test clippy/check frontier still reports tests/obligation_lifecycle_e2e.rs failing where run_test(|| async { ... }) captures channel state by borrow instead of ownership. Scope: fix the affected run_test closures in tests/obligation_lifecycle_e2e.rs by moving the channel state into the async body, preserve harness behavior, and validate with targeted rch-backed cargo check/clippy on that test target. Excludes other remaining compile frontiers such as phase0_verification, golden_outputs, and shared_handle_test.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"IvoryElk","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:37:05.807029713Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","updated_at":"2026-03-08T04:46:39.636204332Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T04:46:39.636182351Z","close_reason":"Completed: changed tests/obligation_lifecycle_e2e.rs to bind the channel receiver mutably in channel_reserve_send_receive so Receiver::try_recv() matches the current &mut self API; validation: rustfmt --check --edition 2024 tests/obligation_lifecycle_e2e.rs, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-obligation-check4 cargo check --test obligation_lifecycle_e2e, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-obligation-clippy4 cargo clippy --test obligation_lifecycle_e2e -- -D warnings, and rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-obligation-test4 cargo test --test obligation_lifecycle_e2e -- --nocapture all passed remotely","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","channel","compile","tests"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.11","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:37:05.807029713Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.110","title":"[audit][service] Preserve self-wake readiness edges in LoadShed::poll_ready","description":"src/service/load_shed.rs treats any inner poll_ready Pending as overload and immediately returns Ready(Ok(())) so call() can shed. If the inner service self-wakes during that poll_ready call, the wake is discarded and LoadShed still sheds the immediately following request even though the backend became ready in the same probe. Mirror the recent load-balance/readiness-edge hardening: probe with a tracking waker, repoll once when self-wake fires during poll_ready, and add a focused regression proving the immediate follow-up call succeeds instead of being falsely overloaded. Validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PinkDune","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:17:52.944036183Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T23:17:52.944036183Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.110","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:17:52.944036183Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.111","title":"[audit][web] Replace ambient session-id entropy with explicit SessionLayer entropy source","description":"src/web/session.rs currently generates session IDs with direct getrandom::fill in generate_session_id(), which bypasses the repo's explicit entropy/capability model and defeats strict entropy isolation. Replace the ambient call with an explicit entropy source owned by SessionLayer (defaulting to OsEntropy), keep session-ID formatting behavior unchanged, add deterministic tests proving injected entropy is used, and update ambient-authority coverage/docs if needed.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BrownTower","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-10T23:18:23.880082530Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T23:18:23.880082530Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","entropy","security","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.111","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:18:23.880082530Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.112","title":"[audit][trace] Remove wall-clock nondeterminism from replay TraceMetadata::new","description":"TraceMetadata::new currently seeds recorded_at from SystemTime::now(), and LabRuntime replay recording uses that constructor directly. That means two identical deterministic runs can still emit different replay metadata and different downstream checkpoint created_at baselines despite identical seeds/events. Fix the root metadata constructor/use path so deterministic replay artifacts default to a stable recorded_at, add focused regressions proving identical construction for identical seeds and stable lab replay metadata, and keep any human-facing formatting tolerant of zero/no-wall-clock timestamps.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PurpleFox","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:19:23.065970320Z","created_by":"PurpleFox","updated_at":"2026-03-10T23:19:23.065970320Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","trace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.112","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:19:23.065970320Z","created_by":"PurpleFox"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.12","title":"[audit][tests] Remove stale mutable receiver bindings in channel partition injection tests","description":"The current rch-backed 'cargo clippy -p asupersync --tests --message-format short --keep-going -- -D warnings' frontier reports three stale bindings in tests/channel_partition_injection.rs where receivers were made mutable during prior mutability repairs but are no longer read. Clean those bindings up so the test target is warning-free again, validate with targeted rch-backed check/clippy/test for channel_partition_injection, and keep the scope limited to that file.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:49:40.293165217Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","updated_at":"2026-03-08T04:54:54.837278970Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T04:54:54.837257971Z","close_reason":"Completed: cleaned tests/channel_partition_injection.rs by keeping mutable receiver bindings only in tests that actually read from the channel and changing the three dead receiver bindings to _rx at the cancellation/evidence/stats sites; validation: rustfmt --check --edition 2024 tests/channel_partition_injection.rs, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-partition-check12b cargo check --test channel_partition_injection, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-partition-clippy12b cargo clippy --test channel_partition_injection -- -D warnings, and rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-partition-test12b cargo test --test channel_partition_injection -- --nocapture all passed remotely","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.12","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:49:40.293165217Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.13","title":"[audit][tests] Remove lock-guard drop extension in shared handle join probe","description":"The current rch-backed 'cargo clippy -p asupersync --tests --message-format short --keep-going -- -D warnings' frontier reports tests/shared_handle_test.rs:73:42 for a temporary with significant Drop in a match scrutinee. Refactor the join-probe branch so the handle lock and try_join call happen outside the match scrutinee, preserving behavior while satisfying clippy. Validate with targeted rch-backed check/clippy/test for shared_handle_test and keep the scope limited to that file.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:55:24.106180172Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","updated_at":"2026-03-08T04:59:15.854236082Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T04:59:15.854217358Z","close_reason":"Completed: refactored tests/shared_handle_test.rs SharedLabHandle::try_join_probe so the handle lock and try_join call occur outside the match scrutinee, preserving ready/none/error behavior while removing the significant_drop_in_scrutinee clippy error; validation: rustfmt --check --edition 2024 tests/shared_handle_test.rs, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-shared-check13 cargo check --test shared_handle_test, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-shared-clippy13 cargo clippy --test shared_handle_test -- -D warnings, and rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-shared-test13 cargo test --test shared_handle_test -- --nocapture all reached remote exit 0","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.13","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:55:24.106180172Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.14","title":"[audit][service] Respect DNS poll interval after resolution failures","description":"DnsServiceDiscovery::poll_discover() increments error_count on resolve failure but leaves last_resolve unchanged. When a hostname is failing, repeated poll_discover() calls therefore retry DNS immediately on every poll instead of honoring poll_interval, which can create hot-loop retry pressure in callers that poll frequently. Fix by recording the failure attempt time, preserving deterministic diff behavior for successful resolutions, and adding a regression test that proves repeated failures within the interval do not increment error_count again until the interval elapses or invalidate() is called.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ScarletRaven","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-08T18:41:46.886779808Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T19:36:05.520817992Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T19:36:05.520798145Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in-tree and released by assignee: src/service/discover.rs now records last_resolve on DNS resolution failure, and the file includes regressions dns_discovery_failed_resolution_respects_poll_interval plus dns_discovery_invalidate_forces_retry_after_failed_resolution. ScarletRaven reported rch-backed cargo check -p asupersync --lib and cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings passing on this slice; narrowed test-target runs remained stuck in the known rch queue/post-run transport path, with no concrete failing output surfaced.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.14","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T18:41:46.886779808Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
